<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Shoppers are going wild over an $87 instant hot water dispenser from Bunnings just a month after Kmart launched its sell out model that heats two litres in seconds.</p>

<p>The $87 gadget instantaneously dispenses 1.8 litres of hot water in just eight seconds without preheating - saving 20 per cent energy compared to a standard kettle.</p>

<p>Those who missed out on Kmart's $79 sold-out version are now heading to the hardware store's online store to get their hands on the product, which comes with a detachable water tank.</p>

